AGI - "I am here at the UN to testify once again how much Italy has trust in the United Nations, and also in its action Mr. Secretary-General. The more crises, difficulties, oppositions and contrasts grow in the world, the more it is said that there is an indispensable need for the action of the UN." These are the words of the President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella, meeting the Secretary General of the UN, Antonio Guterres, at the Glass Palace.
&nbsp;
<div </div
<em>Video by Massimo Basile</em>
&nbsp;
"I am pleased to be able to analyze with you the current crisis, it is necessary at this moment to interrupt everywhere the spirals of violence, the spiral action-reaction makes aggravate the problems, does not allow to solve them," added the Head of State.&nbsp;<span>" Italy is an exemplary partner of the UN," Guterres reiterated. "Italy is a northern country that understands the South." </span
&nbsp;
<span> The United Nations leader then returned to address the issue of conflict in the Middle East. "A land invasion at Rafah would be intolerable, due to its devastating humanitarian consequences and its destabilizing impact in the region." And in Mattarella: "I receive you at a time of great concern. Today I have made a very strong appeal to the government of Israel and the leadership of Hamas to make further effort to make materializing an agreement that is absolutely vital. It is an opportunity that cannot be lost." &nbsp;</span>
